## Team and Reporting

Community Care Services is the department Alec Blair reports to. The interim Executive Director is **Brandy Milbak**. Alec works closely with two business analysts, **Juliane Mueller** and **Breanne Barber**.

**Terminology note**: this area appears under a few names across the vault — "Community Care Services" (the department), "Community Care IT Services" (this folder), and the "IT Community Portfolio" (Alec's remit in [[CLAUDE-HSS]]). Treat these as referring to the same organisational area; the canonical name is still being settled.

## Active Initiative — AI-Assisted Requirements Authoring on GitLab

A pilot is underway (Alec plus the two BAs) to move requirements content — user stories, screen specifications, SBARs, and related artefacts — out of OneNote and into the team's existing **self-hosted GitLab Community Edition**, using each project's **GitLab Wiki** as the Markdown authoring and browsing surface. An AI assistant (Claude Cowork) accelerates authoring against a local clone of the wiki; non-AI team members browse and edit the same pages through GitLab's web interface, with role-based permissions for reviewers and authors. The team would also build reusable prompt "skills" that encode house standards so output stays consistent across authors. The driver is to gain version history, structured review, and cross-linking that OneNote and Word do not provide, while keeping content in an open, portable format on infrastructure already owned and controlled.

The detail lives in [[Microsoft Copilot Cowork Business Case]] (titled for the alternative it argues against; the recommendation is the GitLab-based approach over Microsoft Copilot Cowork and GitHub Copilot).

**Open items to track:**

- Confirm Claude's Cowork seat tier, seat type, and Team-plan seat minimums (may exceed three users) and the resulting per-user cost before committing a figure.
- Validate that processing communicable-disease content through a cloud AI service is acceptable under HIA, and whether an enterprise/no-retention arrangement is required.
- Confirm local working copies on staff workstations are covered by existing endpoint controls (e.g. disk encryption), since the GitLab server remains the master copy.
- Treat OneNote as a one-time migration source: export to Markdown, import to the GitLab Wiki, then retire OneNote as the system of record.

